                  <summary>Collection of Shiʻa and Sunni polemical treatises relating to the
							taʻziyah ritual (a-d)</summary>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 309a" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_309a-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="3r">ff. 1v-3r</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23284">Javāb-i dū ḥadīs̱</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">جواب دو حدیث</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A Shiʻa tract by an unnamed author compiled from Sunni
									authorities legitimising the practice of tearing clothes and
									beating the face during the <term>taʻzīyah</term> ritual. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The title is taken from the heading. </p>
                        <p>Microfilm: IOL Neg 393 </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
										the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <biblScope>
                              <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!38_f057r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/38, f. 57</ref>. 
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 309b" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_309b-item2">
                     <locus from="4r" to="12r">ff. 4r-12r</locus>
                     <author key="person_f7392">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Muḥammad Rashīd al-Dīn Khān
									Dihlavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">محمد رشید الدین خان دهلوی </persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>
                        <p>An untitled Sunni response to Delhi Persian 309a by an author
									identified in a note on f. 4r as <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7392">Mawlavī Rashīd
										al-Dīn Khān</persName> who can presumably be identified with
									Rashīd al-Dīn Dihlavī, known for his anti-Shiʻa works. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Microfilm: IOL Neg 393. </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
										the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <biblScope>
                              <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!38_f055r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/38, f. 55</ref>. 
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 309c" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_309c-item3">
                     <locus from="13v" to="42v">ff. 13v-42v</locus>
                     <author key="person_f8386">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Abū ʻAlī al-Ḥusaynī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">ابو علی الحسینی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23285">Kashf al-ghayn ʻan taʻzīyah
								al-Ḥusayn </title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23285">کشف الغین عن تعزیة الحسین</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A Shiʻa refutation of Delhi Persian 309b on the subject of
									mourning at <term>taʻziyahs</term> by the author of <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="">Kashf al-ghimām ʻan taʻzīyah
										al-imām</title>, ie. <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8386">Abū ʻAlī al-Ḥusaynī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into an introduction, four discourses
										(<term>maqālah</term>) and a conclusion. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Each line is numbered 1-17 in the margin. </p>
                        <p>Microfilm: IOL Neg 394. </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
										the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <biblScope>
                              <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!38_f054r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/38, f. 54</ref>. 
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="Delhi Persian 309d" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_309d-item4">
                     <locus from="43v" to="140v">ff. 43v-140v</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23286">Taṣfīyah al-´an̄āqib ʻan bāb
								taʻziyah Sayyidnā Ḥusayn ibn ʻAlī ibn Abī Ṭālib</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23286">تصفیة العناکب عن باب تعزیة سیّدنا حسین بن علی ابی
								طالب</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A Sunni reply by an unnamed author to the controversy over
									practices at Shiʻa <term>taʻziyas</term>. It is prefaced by an
									introduction in five parts (<term>faṣl</term>). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Microfilm: IOL Neg 395. </p>
                     </note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>R. Levy, <title>Drafts for Catalogue of Persian Manuscripts in
										the India Office Library, vol. III</title>, <biblScope>
                              <ref target="http://www.bl.uk/manuscripts/Viewer.aspx?ref=mss_eur_e207!38_f053r" type="n/a">Mss Eur E207/38, f. 53</ref>. 
                           </biblScope>
                        </bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
